| Chart | Version | Dependencies | Notes |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
{{- range (datasource "charts" | coll.Sort "name") }}
{{- $dir := .path | filepath.Dir -}}
{{- $note := "" -}}
{{- if (has . "annotations") -}}
  {{- $note = .annotations.notes -}}
{{- end -}}
{{- if not $note }}
  {{- range (coll.Slice "NOTES.txt" "NOTES.md") }}
    {{- if file.Exists (filepath.Join $dir .) }}
      {{- $note = (file.Read (filepath.Join $dir .) | strings.TrimSpace | strings.Split "\n" | coll.First) -}}
      {{- break -}}
    {{- end }}
  {{- end }}
{{- end }}
| {{ .name }} | `{{ .version }}` | {{ if (has . "dependencies") }}{{ range $i, $d := .dependencies }}{{ if $i }}, {{ end }}{{ $d.name }} (`{{ $d.version }}`) {{ end }}{{ else }}-{{ end }} | {{ $note | default "-" }} |
{{- end }}

<!-- MATRIX_END -->

## 🤖 Automation & CI/CD

### 🔄 Renovate
We use [Renovate](https://www.mend.io/renovate/) to keep our dependencies up-to-date. It automatically scans the repository for:
- Helm chart versions in `Chart.yaml`
- Container images in `Dockerfile` and values files
- External dependencies in ArgoCD manifests

Updates are proposed via Merge Requests, ensuring our infrastructure stays secure and current.

### 🚀 GitLab CI
The pipeline is designed to:
1. **Build** and push the custom Docker image used for CI tasks.
2. **Package** and push Helm charts from `_charts/` to our OCI registry when changes are detected.
3. **Validate** manifests to ensure deployment stability.

## 🛠️ Local Development

We use [Task](https://taskfile.dev/) as a task runner. Common commands:

```bash
# List all available tasks
task --list-all

# List all Helm charts in the repo
task list:all

# Authenticate with the Helm OCI registry
task auth
```

